Reasoning: The paper deals with problems related to directed graphs (digraphs) and their decomposition. The problem of finding k-distinct in and out branchings in digraphs is a combinatorial optimization problem, which falls under the category of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also introduces a new digraph decomposition called the rooted cut decomposition, which can be seen as a graph theoretic algorithmic technique and hence, the paper can also be classified under the categories of Data Structures (cs.DS), Computational Geometry (cs.CG), Graph Theory (cs.GT), and Computational Complexity (cs.CC).
